                  <summary><p>Paper manuscript from the UVSL [4/66]. Poems written on both sides, separated by blank space, brittle and worm-holed, just legible (on very brown paper in black in – laminated), few variants between the lines in the same hand, many underlined words and phrases.</p>
<p>Complete (except AN 336.19d–343.15c), misnumbered from 107 onwards; with traditional colophon (p. 258f.).</p>
<p>Closely agreeing with other mss, i.e. TT, NL, C1, C5, G1, G2.</p></summary>
                  
